						               													<description>Players sit in a circle and place the game bell in the center and decide on the length of the game (i.e. how many cards to claim).  Short games are 3-4 cards while longer games consist of 6-7 card totals.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players are contestants that answer ten rapid fire yes or no questions without hesitation to claim (win) the card.  The trick is that contestants are not allowed to simply say &amp;quot;yes&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;no&amp;quot; nor repeat any of their previous answers from the round.  When answering the question, a player needs to think of an answer that goes beyond a simple yes or no.  For example, a contestant may be asked &amp;quot;Do you like ice hockey?&amp;quot;  An appropriate response could be &amp;quot;More than baseball&amp;quot;.  When rules are broken, other players ding the bell and steal the card.  The contestant with the most cards at the end of the game is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
